LAFIA – Hon. Ibrahim Balarabe-Abdullahi, the speaker Nasarawa State House of Assembly, on Monday, charged lawmakers in the state to live above board in the discharge of their responsibilities. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The speaker gave the task while announcing the names of the 22 House standing committee at the floor of the House in Lafia. The members of the committees are committee chairmen, Rules and Business to be chaired by Hon Tanko Tunga, the Majority Leader of the House, Hon Danladi Jatau, the Minority Leader of the House is to chair Public Complaints and Petitions, Works and Transport is to be chaired by Hon Abdullazeez Danladi and Education, Science and Technology is to be chaired by Hon Daniel Ogazi. Others are Public Accounts committee Hon. Abdullahi Angibi, Finance and Appropriation committee Hon Aliyu Dogara and the chairman, Local Government committee is Hon Mohammed Alkali, Lands and Survey committee is to be chaired by Hon David Maiyaki. Others are Hon. Mohammed Muluku as the chairman, House Committee on Planning, Budget and SDGs; Hon Mohammed Bello is the chairman, House Committee on Capital Market/Commerce and Industry and House committee on Youths and Sports is to be chaired by Musa Iyimoga,” he said. The speaker also announced Hon Usman Shafa as chairman, House Committee on Health, Hon Ali Nana, chairman, House Committee on Public Service and Pilgrims while Women Affairs committee is to be chaired by Hon Samuel Tsebe.